However I also think that humans in general have been living on borrowed time anyways.<br>
<br>
There is a large rock about half the size of earth's moon heading toward us.  From what I understand it could be a near miss or a hit in 2029 or there abouts.<br>
<br>
Many of you will laugh, many will half believe me and dismiss this as a stupid joke, and still others that believe will think.. &quot;oh 26 years away?  Who cares thats too far away to worry about&quot;.  Well this rock missed the earth on its last pass by, I for one hope it misses again since I want to hold out hope human kind might have some chance at becoming less &quot;sucky&quot;.  No matter how you look at it though we are living on borrowed time.<br>
<br>
Considering that people do suck I am at times tempted to not care if that rock or another one hits.  At times though I remind myself that for all he millions of us that suck there is 1 real, &quot;decent&quot; person.  That person is not me nor is it you, of that I can be mostly sure... but they are out there and with luck they will breed and we will not.<br>
